<HEADER>
A6424 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-BRONCOS-GORDON-BO     02-01 0344
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-BRONCOS-GORDON-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GORDON CUTS RIGHT IN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By WILL McDONOUGH  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI _ The way Darrien Gordon saw it, Chris Chandler tried to
dance the dance but didn't have any rhythm.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought Chandler had happy feet,'' said Gordon after he
intercepted two of Chandler's passes to key a stout defensive
effort in Denver's 34-19 victory over Atlanta Sunday night in the
Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Happy feet is the expression players use to desribe a
quarterback whose nerves have taken over his body under pressure.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our front four had good pressure on Chandler all day,'' said
Gordon, who also had two interceptions against the Jets in the AFC
Championship Game two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   Gordon says Chandler felt the pressure and couldn't respond.
``We did a good job of disguising what we were doing on defense,''
he said. ``We showed him a look like we were going to play zone,
and we blitzed him. Then we showed him a blitz, and we played zone.
We tried to make Chandler beat us and he couldn't do it.
</P>
<P>
   ``As a defense we were determined not to let their running game
beat us. We wanted to put it all on Chandler. Our defensive line,
and our blitzing, caused him problems. There were times when he
wasn't sure what he wanted to do with the ball.''
</P>
<P>
   Denver did a nice job of bringing pressure up the middle.
</P>
<P>
   In the heat of Miami, the Broncos rotated their defensive
linemen throughout the game, keeping them fresh. Often, they put
their taller linemen in the middle of the rush, and several times
they were able to knock down Chandler passes. The first
interception he threw came off a deflection by defensive end Keith
Traylor, which Gordon picked off on the fly.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was really disappointed with myself after the second
interception,'' said Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   ``I should have taken it all the way back for a touchdown. But I
ran out of gas and Chandler tackled me. That was really
embarrassing when he tackled me in the open field, but I was just
tired and lost my legs.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
