<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RONNING PUTS HEART INTO UPSTART PREDATORS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE _ When he got traded here on Halloween for future
considerations,  &UR; Cliff
 &UR; Ronning admitted he was crushed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sure I was. I used to eat and breathe Coyotes,'' the veteran
center said. ``But I think you have to put your whole heart into a
team like that or you won't be the best you can be.''
</P>
<P>
   He's doing the same thing now with the expansion Nashville
Predators, and thanks largely in part to him, the first-year club
has a legitimate chance to make the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes, who for whatever reason didn't think he was the
answer anymore, aren't only headed toward the postseason but are
viewed by many as a Stanley Cup contender. Ronning, however, isn't
upset about not being along for the ride.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not a jealous person,'' he said. ``It's kind of funny,
actually. I'm happy for a lot of the players there. I've become
close with some of them.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been an adjustment here, but it's been fun to come to a
team that works hard. It's a young team and I'm the oldest guy. But
everything's an experience. There's reasons why I'm here and I feel
I belong.''
</P>
<P>
   The Predators are about to keep him around awhile longer, too.
During the next few days, they are expected to announce they have
re-signed Ronning for another two to three years. &QL; 
JR and TD &QL; 
The Coyotes were giving center  &UR; Jeremy Roenick a hard time before
the game after it was learned he and Denver Broncos running back
 &UR; Terrell Davis were on the same betting board at the Imperial
Palace. The bet: Would Roenick score more points against Nashville
than Davis scores touchdowns against the Atlanta Falcons in
Sunday's Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   ``I got two today, but I'd say it's going to be pretty close to
a push here,'' Roenick said, laughing. ``I think TD could have a
big night, though.''
</P>
<P>
   Roenick won the line, as Davis failed to score during Denver's
Super Bowl victory. &QL; 
You again?
</P>
<P>
   When the Coyotes acquired defenseman  &UR; J.J. Daigneault from the
Predators, the first team he faced was Nashville. Sunday marked he
second time in eight games he went up against his former teammates.
</P>
<P>
   ``The first time, it was pretty emotional,'' Daigneault said.
``This time, it was just taking care of business and trying to play
solid, defensively. Toward the end, after we had a three-goal lead,
I think I got a little bit overconfident and I wanted to
stickhandle a little bit too much.''
</P>
<P>
   He also almost got into a scrum with ex-teammate  &UR; Drew
Berehowsky. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-01-99 0141EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
