<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, January 29
-- Court Reproduction Services Inc. of Philadelphia won a $192,220
contract from the Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C.,
for printing services.
</P>
<P>
   United Terex Inc. of Fairview Village won a $144,477 contract
from the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for
aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co. Inc. of Bristol won a $57,749 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for bearings.
</P>
<P>
   VIZ Manufacturing Co. of Philadelphia won a $298,585 contract
from the Dept. of Commerce in Silver Spring, Md., for electrical
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   North American Manufacturing Co. of Scranton won a $2 million
contract from the Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia
for waist straps.
</P>
<P>
   Litton Systems Inc. of Williamsport won a $118,365 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for electrical
components.
</P>
<P>
   Wheeler Brothers Inc. of Somerset won a $83,545 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for glass.
</P>
<P>
   Mozip Sign Co. of Kingston won a $57,674 contract from the
Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C., for printing
services.
</P>
<P>
   Derbyshire Machine and Tool Co. of Philadelphia won a $239,708
contract from the Navy in Mechanicsburg, Pa., for valves.
</P>
