<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MARY' IS SOMETHING, AND SO IS JACKIE CHAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``There's Something About Mary'' _ The Farrelly
brothers, aided and abetted by the brilliant and beautiful Cameron
Diaz and the oddly evasive Ben Stiller, create a good comedy that's
in bad taste. It's just the kind of bad taste that made ``Animal
House'' the gross-out film by which all others must be measured.
Life with the Partridge Family and the Brady Bunch was never like
this.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jackie Chan's Who Am I?'' _ Chan's clan will flock to the
video stores to catch this latest high-action flick. But others
might appreciate the superb action sequences and breathtaking
stunts while Chan deals with an international spy ring as only he
can.
</P>
<P>
   ``Life and Death on Long Island'' _ One of the smartest,
funniest films of 1998 features a surprisingly effective Jason
Priestley as the object of John Hurt's affection. Brilliant, witty,
and remarkable.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BLACK HISTORY MONTH: MPI Home Video, which boasts an impressive
African-American catalog, highlights some titles for February.
``Muhammad Ali: In His Own Words'' ($19.98) is a marvelous and
intelligent collage of Ali's public addresses. Quick-witted,
intelligent, and informed, this is a look at a man many people
believe is the most significant international figure of the late
20th century. ``Only the Ball Was White'' ($19.98) documents the
days of the Negro Leagues, when African-Americans were banned from
the white leagues. Satchel Paige and Buck Leonard are among those
interviewed. ``Martin Luther King: Commemorative Collection''
($29.98) highlights the speeches and accomplishments of the great
civil rights leader. Team it with ``Malcolm X: Making It Plain''
($29.98), a magnificent documentary on the life of the political
philosopher. Call 800-777-2223 to order directly or for a catalog.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Feb. 9: ``Antz,'' ``Legionnaire,'' ``Next
Stop Wonderland,'' ``Rounders,'' ``The Scarlet Tunic.'' Feb. 16:
``Snake Eyes,'' ``Beyond Silence,'' ``First Love, Last Rites,''
``The Governess,'' ``This Is the Sea,'' ``Without Limits.'' Feb.
23: ``Ronin,'' ``Carnival of Souls,'' ``The Manchurian Candidate,''
``Pecker.'' March 2: ``Dark City,'' ``Tom and Jerry: The Movie,''
``A Winter Tan,'' ``The Island of Dr. Moreau.'' March 9: ``What
Dreams May Come,'' ``Dead Man on Campus,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``Slam,''
``Somebody Is Waiting.'' March 16: ``The Waterboy,'' ``Bulworth,''
``No Laughing Matter,'' ``Living Out Loud,'' ``One True Thing,''
``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul Monette: The Brink of Summer's End,''
``Who the Hell Is Juliette?,'' ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit.''
March 23: ``Pleasantville,'' ``Firelight,'' ``Bride of Chucky,''
``Jerry Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn 2,''
``Strike!'' March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,'' ``Mutual Needs.''
April 6: ``The Dentist 2.'' April 27: ``Happiness.''
</P>
</TEXT>
