<P>
   JORDAN-ABDULLAH _ AMMAN, Jordan _ No one expected that young
Prince Abdullah of Jordan would someday be in line to be king, back
in 1993, when he got married. But the young prince gave the
thousands of wedding guests something to remember: one of his army
buddies parachuted into the crowded palace gardens and cut the
wedding cake with a sword. People here hope that the traits that
make him like his father, from his flamboyance to his military
background, will give him what it takes to be king. But, he'll have
to get over his obvious discomfort in the spotlight and improve his
Arabic. Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
