<P>
   NJ-DEATH-PENALTY (Trenton, N.J.) _ The New Jersey Supreme Court
has upheld the state's death penalty law, rejecting a claim that
black felons were at greater risk of receiving the death sentence
than whites. The court deliberated on the matter for two years and
had appointed a retired judge to conduct a study on the death
penalty as applied to blacks and whites. He found a nearly equal
percentage of blacks and whites accused of capital crimes received
the death sentence. By David Kocieniewski.
