<HEADLINE>
TRAVEL BARGAINS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sunday, Feb. 7)  
(mk) 
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   INTRODUCING ORLANDO: Spirit Airlines will begin daily nonstop
service to Orlando, Fla., from Newark, N.J., International Airport
on March 4, and is offering an introductory one-way fare of $69 for
all tickets that are purchased by midnight Feb. 28. The Newark
flights will depart at 2:20 p.m. and arrive at 5:10; the return
flight departs at 10:40 a.m. and arrives at 1:30. The airline,
based in Detroit, will use a DC-9 on the route. Reservations: (800)
772-7117.
</P>
<P>
   CALLING FOR SAVINGS: Four Seasons Hotels and Resorts and AT&AMP;T
have teamed up in a City Pleasures program that gives guests a $100
savings certificate with each stay of two or more consecutive
nights at one of 22 participating hotels through March 31. To be
eligible, guests must present AT&AMP;T calling cards when they check
in. The savings certificates (one per room) can be applied to a
guest's current stay, future stays, room upgrades, spa treatments
and hotel dining, or purchases of hotel bathrobes. Groups are not
eligible. Four Seasons reservations: (800) 474-5806; guests need to
mention the City Pleasures certificate and the AT&AMP;T calling card
when making reservations.
</P>
<P>
   EARLY BIRD BARGES: For travelers who are willing to take their
chances with the weather on a barge in Burgundy in March, a
reservations service called B&AMP;V Waterways has a package for $1,990
a person, double occupancy. The price includes a six-night cruise,
round-trip air fare between New York and Paris, an overnight stay
in Paris, and a half-day cruise on the Seine. The barge is
Continental Waterways' 22-passenger Caprice, cruising from Dijon to
Fleurey-sur-Ouche, Gissey-sur-Ouche and Vandenesse-en-Auxois. The
boat has central heating throughout, and cabins have private baths.
There are bikes on board for passengers' use. Departures are on
March 6 and 13. Information and reservations: (800) 676-6613.
</P>
<P>
   HAWAII CRUISE: Holland America Line has a 16-day Circle Hawaii
Cruise from San Diego to Vancouver that starts at $2,199 a person
for an inside stateroom and $2,549 a person for an outside
stateroom, double occupancy, including port charges and taxes.
Round-trip air fare from New York is an additional $729 a person.
The cruise, which departs April 30 on the 1,266-passenger
Statendam, calls at Ensenada, Mexico; Kona, on the Big Island of
Hawaii; Lahaina, Maui; Honolulu, Oahu; Nawiliwili, Kauai, and Hilo,
Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
   Optional shore excursions (starting around $40) include
Haleakala Crater on Maui, river kayaking on Kauai and Volcanoes
National Park on the Big Island of Hawaii. The itinerary includes
nine days at sea. For more information: (800) 426-0327. (The line
prefers reservations through travel agents.) On the Internet:
www.hollandamerica.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
