city government after colleagues complained about his use of the
word ``niggardly.'' Howard's comment, from a New York Times
interview, was gleaned by Carolyn Hall.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``I love money. I could make more beautiful objects if I had &LR; 
 &UR; more money. But if you think about it too much, then it doesn't &LR; 
 &UR; help your art.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - Architect  &UR; Philip Johnson &LR; , 92, in Esquire magazine.
</P>
