   ART-MATISSE-PICASSO &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Henri Matisse and Pablo Picasso were more
than just the leading figures of 20th century modern art _ they
were rivals and admirers, drawing upon each other's work in their
own. The Kimbell Art Museum's new Matisse and Picasso exhibit, the
first major show pairing the two artists in more than 50 years,
opened Sunday. It promises to shed light on how these icons created
some of the world's most enduring modern art works. By JANET TYSON.
Story will move in ``e'' arts and entertainment category.
(Accompanied by KIMBELL-EXHIBIT.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
