   TV-AFRICAN AMERICAN-ART &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The six-hour PBS series ``I'll Make Me a World: A
Century of African-American Arts,'' which began Monday and
continues Tuesday and Wednesday, had long envisioned it as a
catalyst for national discussion on black arts. Even as it serves
up the engaging personal tales of a selective group of
African-American artists, it clearly illustrates the challenges
facing black artists: namely, must they always portray only the
positive aspects of black America. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
