<HEADLINE>
THE GROOM IS RED IS BEATEN
</HEADLINE>
   (ms) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HALLANDALE, Fla. _ The Groom Is Red, winner of the Champagne
Stakes at Belmont Park last fall, made his 1999 debut Monday and
found the road to the Kentucky Derby just as challenging as
advertised. He ran third behind Certain, who won a star-filled
allowance at Gulfstream Park for his fourth consecutive victory.
</P>
<P>
   Certain ran second in his first two starts last year, then won
three in a row at nearby Calder. He ran Monday as third choice to
The Groom Is Red, who won the Champagne on a sloppy track but
failed Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He didn't have any early speed, which is usual with him,''
said Jerry Bailey, who rode The Groom Is Red. ``He made a good move
around the stretch turn, but then he just couldn't sustain it.''
</P>
<P>
   Certain ran the mile and one-sixteenth around two turns in 1:46
2/5 under Shane Sellers, and paid $8.20 for a $2 bet to win. At the
finish, he led another Zito horse, Cryptodiplomacy, by three and
one-quarter lengths, with The Groom Is Red a length and a quarter
back in third.
</P>
</TEXT>
