   CLINTON-BUDGET (Washington) _ President Clinton touts his $1.77
trillion proposed budget and its bailouts for Social Security and
Medicare as relief for Generation X, which faces the risk of high
federal taxes to subsidize the retirement of the post-World War II
generation. By STEWART M. POWELL, JUDY HOLLAND And JENNIFER CORBETT
DOOREN. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACHMENT-CLINTON (Washington) _ Monica Lewinsky is
interviewed by congressional prosecutors while lawyers for
President Clinton complain in federal court that Independent
Counsel Kenneth Starr had illegally leaked information to the news
media. By JOHN C. HENRY.
