   CALIFORNIA-BUDGET (Washington) _ The Pentagon is seeking $296.8
million for new military construction projects in California for
the fiscal year beginning Oct. 1, according to the Clinton
administration's budget proposal released Monday, a $75.3 million
increase over the current year. Only Hawaii _ at $324.6 million _
would receive more military construction money. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
(Already filed.)
