   LOCKHEED-COMSAT (Bethesda, Md.) _ Lockheed Martin's planned
purchase of Comsat, the quasi-government satellite company, would
put the defense contractor into the big leagues of the global
telecommunications business. But Comsat owns 19 percent of
Intelsat, an intergovernmental satellite network that Congress now
wants to privatize. To pull off the Comsat merger, Lockheed is
caught in the larger issue of Intelsat deregulation. By Leslie
Wayne.
