Advisors, the $3 billion New York-based hedge fund, after a
tumultuous year that saw it drop more than 20 percent in last
summer's downdraft. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
<P>
   SUPERBOWL-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Many of the 51 paid commercials
that ran nationally during the Super Bowl _ 48 shown one time each,
plus three repeats _ were replete with bathroom humor, along with
other crude, common, cornball imagery. Perhaps that's why Super
Sunday turned out to be even more of a misnomer than usual. By
Stuart Elliott.
