<SLUG> BC-RICH-NYTIMES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FRANK RICH GETTING DUAL ROLE AT THE NEW YORK TIMES 
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Frank Rich, whose column has appeared on The New York
Times' Op-Ed page twice a week since January 1994, will write
longer articles for the page and become a regular contributor to
The Times Magazine. This arrangement was announced on Monday by
Arthur Sulzberger Jr., publisher of the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   Times editors said the new arrangement was a response to Rich's
desire to write essays and articles lengthier than the 700-word
Op-Ed format would permit. Starting in June, he will write a
1,400-word opinion article for the Op-Ed page every other Saturday.
He will also write articles and commentaries for the magazine on a
variety of subjects.
</P>
<P>
   Joseph Lelyveld, the executive editor, said Rich would
``continue to be a major cultural critic in every possible sense.''
Rich joined The Times in 1980 and served as its chief theater
critic for 13 years before becoming a columnist.
</P>
<P>
   Journal, Rich's 700-word column, will appear until Feb. 13. He
will then take a four-month leave to finish a memoir for Random
House and will return in June.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
