<SLUG> BC-OBIT-WALSH-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MASON WALSH, 86, PUBLISHER
</HEADLINE>
   (ms) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ Mason Walsh, a former publisher of The Arizona
Republic and The Phoenix Gazette, died Jan. 30 of complications
from pneumonia. He was 86 and lived in Scottsdale, Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   In 1966, he became general manager of the Arizona papers and in
1975 was given the additional job of assistant publisher. He was
named publisher of the papers in 1978, was made publisher emeritus
in 1980 and retired in 1981. Walsh was a past president of the
Associated Press Managing Editors Association.
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by his wife, Anne; a daughter, Peggy, and two
sons, Timothy and Kevin.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
